<h1>Solr Maintenance</h1>
<ul>
  <li>
    <a tal:attributes="href string:${request/URL}/clear" href="#">
      Clear Solr Index
    </a><br />
    Clear all data from Solr, i.e. delete all indexed objects
  </li>
  <li>
    <a tal:attributes="href string:${request/URL}/reindex" href="#">
      Reindex Solr Index
    </a><br />
    Find all contentish objects (meaning all objects derived from one of the catalog mixin classes) and (re)indexes them.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a tal:attributes="href string:${request/URL}/sync" href="#">
      Sync Solr Index
    </a><br />
    Sync the Solr index with the portal catalog. Records contained in the catalog but not in Solr will be indexed and records not contained in the catalog will be removed.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a tal:attributes="href string:${request/URL}/cleanup" href="#">
      Cleanup Solr Index
    </a><br />
    Remove entries from solr that don't have a corresponding Zope object or have a different UID than the real object.
  </li>
  <li>
    <a tal:attributes="href string:${request/URL}/optimize" href="#">
      Optimize Solr Indexes
    </a><br />
    Optimizing 'defragments' your index. The space taken by deleted document data is reclaimed and can merge the index into fewer segments. This can improve search performance a lot.
  </li>
</ul>
